<!-- ============ OVERVIEW ============ -->
<Section id="what-is-this" num="01">
  <h2 class="cli-call" data-section-name="What Is This System?"><span class="section-label">What Is This System?</span><span class="cli-line"><span class="fn">Read</span><span class="op">(</span><span class="str">"what_is_this_system"</span><span class="op">)</span><span class="cli-cursor"></span></span></h2>
  <div class="line-numbered">
  <p class="lead">A research automation platform built around <strong>Minty</strong>, an AI research management agent running on a dedicated Mac Studio. 17 background daemons <span class="t-cyan">fetch</span>, <span class="t-green">classify</span>, <span class="t-yellow">ingest</span>, <span class="t-purple">index</span>, <span class="t-pink">summarize</span>, and <span class="t-blue">distribute</span> academic content &mdash; plus enable deep multi-agent corpus analysis. Research superpowers, not a replacement for researchers.</p>

  <p>External sources (<span class="t-cyan">Twitter</span>, <span class="t-green">arXiv</span>, <span class="t-yellow">RSS</span>, <span class="t-purple">Substack</span>, <span class="t-pink">Bluesky</span>, <span class="t-blue">email</span>) are fetched, classified by Claude Opus, and posted to Slack. Papers are <span class="t-cyan">downloaded</span>, <span class="t-green">converted to markdown</span>, <span class="t-yellow">embedded</span> in a vector database, <span class="t-purple">analyzed</span> across 41 semantic dimensions, and made <span class="t-pink">searchable</span> via a Slack bot. A daily digest reaches 29 lab members across 11 institutions.</p>
  </div>
</Section>

<!-- ============ CONTENT PIPELINE ============ -->
<Section id="content-pipeline" num="02">
  <h2 class="cli-call" data-section-name="The Content Pipeline"><span class="section-label">The Content Pipeline</span><span class="cli-line"><span class="fn">Agent</span><span class="op">(</span><span class="str">"trace the content pipeline"</span><span class="op">,</span> <span class="kw">subagent_type</span><span class="op">=</span><span class="str">"Explore"</span><span class="op">)</span><span class="cli-cursor"></span></span></h2>
  <p class="lead">All content flows through <code>#firehose</code> &mdash; two daemons write to it, three read from it. Source: <a href="https://github.com/mint-philosophy/minty-private">minty-private</a> under <code>daemons/pipeline/</code>.</p>

  <!-- Flow summary: 7-stage pipeline overview -->
  <div style="margin:28px 0 24px">
    <div class="pipeline-flow">
      <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--cyan);cursor:pointer"
           data-ingest-tip="6 fetchers pull from Twitter, arXiv, RSS/Substack, Bluesky, Email, and LinkedIn in parallel via a thread pool. A PhilPapers scraper is also available for periodic runs."
           data-ingest-color="#22d3ee">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--cyan)">Sources</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">6 parallel fetchers</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--mint);cursor:pointer"
           data-ingest-tip="Claude Opus scores 6 dimensions (relevance, quality, authority, novelty, actionability, engagement), generates a 5&ndash;10 word headline, assigns one of 16 categories, and explains its reasoning. 16 parallel workers, ~40K tokens per batch."
           data-ingest-color="#2ec4b6">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--mint)">Classify</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">Opus, 6 dimensions</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--amber);cursor:pointer"
           data-ingest-tip="Seth reviews #feed-{day} channels each morning. Thumbs-up promotes items to #firehose via the feed-promote daemon, which polls every 5 minutes."
           data-ingest-color="#f59e0b">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--amber)">Curate</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">Human review</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pf-card pf-hub" style="border-left:3px solid var(--cyan);cursor:pointer"
           data-ingest-tip="Central hub. Everything curated lands here. Three downstream daemons read from it: news-pdf-bot, corpus-ingest, and yesterday-in-ai."
           data-ingest-color="#22d3ee">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--cyan)">#firehose</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">Central hub</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--purple);cursor:pointer"
           data-ingest-tip="news-pdf-bot attaches PDFs via 3-tier acquisition (pattern matching, thread expansion, sandboxed Claude agent). corpus-ingest runs an 11-stage pipeline: markdown conversion, embedding, metadata extraction, cataloguing."
           data-ingest-color="#a78bfa">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--purple)">Ingest</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">PDFs + corpus pipeline</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--indigo);cursor:pointer"
           data-ingest-tip="corpus-agent performs deep semantic analysis on ingested papers: 41 analytical questions, thematic clustering, cross-paper connection mapping."
           data-ingest-color="#818cf8">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--indigo)">Analyse</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">41Q deep analysis</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--pink);cursor:pointer"
           data-ingest-tip="yesterday-in-ai generates a daily narrative digest for subscribers and posts to #mint-community. A weekly Minty's Week in AI summary is produced for lab meetings."
           data-ingest-color="#f472b6">
        <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--pink)">Report</div>
        <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">Daily + weekly digests</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="margin-top:28px;font-size:14px;color:var(--cyan)">Intake Path 1: Automated Discovery</h3>

  <p>The <strong>feedme-daily</strong> daemon runs daily, fetching from six source types in parallel via a thread pool:</p>

  <RefTable>
    <thead><tr><th>Source</th><th>Method</th><th>Window</th><th>Max Items</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Twitter/X</td><td>API v2 (OAuth1)</td><td>24h</td><td>200</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bluesky</td><td>Feed API</td><td>24h</td><td>200</td></tr>
      <tr><td>RSS/Substack</td><td>Feed parser</td><td>7 days</td><td>30</td></tr>
      <tr><td>arXiv</td><td>API</td><td>5 days</td><td>50</td></tr>
      <tr><td>LinkedIn</td><td>Browser automation</td><td>100 posts</td><td>50</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Email newsletters</td><td>Gmail API</td><td>7 days</td><td>30</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </RefTable>

  <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin:18px 0;padding:14px 16px;background:var(--bg-0);border:1px solid var(--border)">
    <div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-3);letter-spacing:0.5px">RAW ITEMS</div>
    <div style="color:var(--text-3);font-family:var(--font)">&#x2192;</div>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:4px;flex-wrap:wrap">
      <code style="font-size:10px;padding:2px 6px;background:var(--bg-3);color:var(--cyan);border:1px solid rgba(34,211,238,0.2)">Content hash</code>
      <code style="font-size:10px;padding:2px 6px;background:var(--bg-3);color:var(--cyan);border:1px solid rgba(34,211,238,0.2)">URL hash</code>
      <code style="font-size:10px;padding:2px 6px;background:var(--bg-3);color:var(--cyan);border:1px solid rgba(34,211,238,0.2)">Canonical IDs</code>
    </div>
    <div style="color:var(--text-3);font-family:var(--font)">&#x2192;</div>
    <div style="cursor:pointer;font-size:11px;color:var(--mint);font-weight:600;border-bottom:1px dashed var(--mint)" data-ingest-tip="Union-find algorithm: items sharing ANY key (content hash, URL, arXiv ID, DOI, YouTube ID) are grouped together. The canonical item is chosen by engagement, then length, then timestamp." data-ingest-color="#2ec4b6">Union-Find</div>
    <div style="color:var(--text-3);font-family:var(--font)">&#x2192;</div>
    <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-2)">best by <span style="color:var(--amber)">engagement</span> &gt; <span style="color:var(--cyan)">length</span> &gt; <span style="color:var(--text-3)">time</span></div>
    <div style="color:var(--text-3);font-family:var(--font)">&#x2192;</div>
    <div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:700;color:var(--green);letter-spacing:0.5px">UNIQUE ITEMS</div>
  </div>

  <p><strong>Classification</strong> uses Claude Opus with 16 concurrent workers in ~40K-token batches. Each item is scored across six dimensions:</p>

  <RefTable>
    <thead><tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Weight</th><th>What It Measures</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td style="color:var(--mint)">Relevance</td><td>0.30</td><td>Topic match to MINT Lab interests &mdash; 30+ specific areas from normative competence to political economy, with explicit scoring guidance per topic</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="color:var(--cyan)">Quality</td><td>0.25</td><td>Substance vs. noise. Length-agnostic: a concise tweet with genuine insight scores as well as a long paper</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="color:var(--indigo)">Authority</td><td>0.15</td><td>Author/institution credibility. Named labs (Anthropic, DeepMind, etc.) score 0.9+</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="color:var(--purple)">Novelty</td><td>0.15</td><td>Breaking news to stale content</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="color:var(--amber)">Actionability</td><td>0.10</td><td>Urgency and time-sensitivity</td></tr>
      <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Engagement</td><td>0.05</td><td>Social proof normalized to platform norms (weak signal)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </RefTable>

  <div style="margin:16px 0 20px">
    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text-3);letter-spacing:0.5px;margin-bottom:10px">COMPOSITE SCORE THRESHOLDS</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:90px 1fr 44px;gap:6px 12px;align-items:center;font-size:11px">
      <div style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600">arXiv</div>
      <div style="background:var(--bg-0);height:6px;position:relative;border:1px solid var(--border)"><div style="position:absolute;left:0;top:0;height:100%;width:60%;background:var(--green);opacity:0.5"></div></div>
      <div style="color:var(--text-2)">&ge; 0.60</div>
      <div style="color:var(--text-1);font-weight:600">Default</div>
      <div style="background:var(--bg-0);height:6px;position:relative;border:1px solid var(--border)"><div style="position:absolute;left:0;top:0;height:100%;width:50%;background:var(--accent);opacity:0.4"></div></div>
      <div style="color:var(--text-2)">&ge; 0.50</div>
      <div style="color:var(--purple);font-weight:600">PhilPapers</div>
      <div style="background:var(--bg-0);height:6px;position:relative;border:1px solid var(--border)"><div style="position:absolute;left:0;top:0;height:100%;width:45%;background:var(--purple);opacity:0.5"></div></div>
      <div style="color:var(--text-2)">&ge; 0.45</div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:10px;display:flex;gap:16px;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:11px;color:var(--text-3)">
      <span><code style="font-size:10px">progress_studies</code> <code style="font-size:10px">ai_science</code> <span style="color:var(--amber)">+0.06 boost</span></span>
      <span>Allowlisted accounts <span style="color:var(--green)">bypass classification</span></span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="margin-top:28px;font-size:14px;color:var(--mint)">Inside the Classification Prompt</h3>
  <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-2);margin-bottom:16px">Every item is evaluated against a 177-line classification prompt encoding the lab's identity, topic taxonomy, quality heuristics, scoring floors, and hard exclusions. Tap or hover each theme for exact prompt language.</p>

  <div class="prompt-grid">
    <div class="prompt-item" style="--pi-color:var(--mint)">
      <span class="prompt-icon">~$</span>
      <div class="prompt-label"><span class="prompt-title">Lab Identity &amp; Mission</span><span class="prompt-sub">Framed around institutional renewal</span></div>
      <div class="prompt-detail">Anchors every classification in the lab's institutional identity and research mission. From the prompt: <em>'You are a research feed classifier for the MINT Research Lab at Johns Hopkins University, directed by Seth Lazar. The lab works on AI safety, normative competence of LLMs, agentic AI governance, and political philosophy of AI.'</em> And: <em>'The lab's research is situated within a broader concern: liberal democracies face institutional, economic, and cultural decline. AI offers the best opportunity to reverse this trajectory &mdash; but only if deployed wisely.'</em></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prompt-item" style="--pi-color:var(--cyan)">
      <span class="prompt-icon">[]</span>
      <div class="prompt-label"><span class="prompt-title">Topic Taxonomy</span><span class="prompt-sub">30+ equally weighted interest areas</span></div>
      <div class="prompt-detail">Defines 30+ equally weighted interest areas &mdash; the classifier must not treat any as 'core' vs. 'peripheral.' From the prompt: <em>'ALL of these interests are equally important: normative competence, benchmark methodology, agent governance, calibrated safety, catastrophic risk, AI and democracy, AI policy, agent security, interpretability, AI economics, platform governance, frontier lab developments, progress studies, advancement of science, abundance agenda, institutional dysfunction/reform...'</em> And: <em>'Domestic and international politics ONLY when about structural/institutional change. Exclude: commentary about individual politicians, horse-race coverage, partisan debates.'</em></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prompt-item" style="--pi-color:var(--indigo)">
      <span class="prompt-icon">&gt;&lt;</span>
      <div class="prompt-label"><span class="prompt-title">Quality Over Length</span><span class="prompt-sub">Density of insight, not word count</span></div>
      <div class="prompt-detail">Explicitly counteracts length bias &mdash; judges density of insight, not word count. From the prompt: <em>'Substance can come in ANY length. A concise post with a genuine insight, novel argument, important evidence, or breaking news is high quality regardless of word count.'</em> And: <em>'A 280-character post making a genuine point is better than a long rehash.'</em> And: <em>'Do NOT penalize reshares/link-posts if the underlying content is relevant and substantive. Judge what's being pointed to, not just the wrapper.'</em></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prompt-item" style="--pi-color:var(--amber)">
      <span class="prompt-icon">^^</span>
      <div class="prompt-label"><span class="prompt-title">Boosted Sources</span><span class="prompt-sub">Scoring floors for key sources</span></div>
      <div class="prompt-detail">Sets scoring floors for strategically important sources &mdash; frontier model releases, trusted authors, and global labs. From the prompt: <em>'New foundation model releases from ANY lab worldwide &mdash; score 0.85+ relevance. This includes video/image/audio models, not just language models.'</em> And: <em>'Chinese labs (DeepSeek, ByteDance/Doubao, Baidu ERNIE, Alibaba Qwen, Zhipu GLM, Moonshot/Kimi, 01.AI/Yi) &mdash; score 0.85+. Track the global frontier, not just Western labs.'</em></div>
    </div>
    <div class="prompt-item" style="--pi-color:var(--purple)">
      <span class="prompt-icon">&phi;</span>
      <div class="prompt-label"><span class="prompt-title">PhilPapers</span><span class="prompt-sub">Topic relevance over journal prestige</span></div>
      <div class="prompt-detail">Specialised handling for philosophy papers &mdash; topic relevance and abstract quality trump journal prestige. From the prompt: <em>'Seth is interested in philosophy of AI broadly &mdash; he wants to see what's being published in this space, even from lesser-known journals and authors.'</em> And: <em>'Judge primarily on TOPIC RELEVANCE and ABSTRACT QUALITY, not journal prestige.'</em> AI consciousness, model welfare, and AI personhood all score 0.8+ relevance.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="prompt-item" style="--pi-color:var(--pink)">
      <span class="prompt-icon">--</span>
      <div class="prompt-label"><span class="prompt-title">Hard Exclusions</span><span class="prompt-sub">Crypto, hype, ethics-slop, marketing</span></div>
      <div class="prompt-detail">Explicit exclusion list that prevents noise from reaching the team. From the prompt: <em>'anti_interest: hype, crypto, celebrity gossip, partisan political commentary, culture war, ethics-slop, marketing emails, promotional content, webinar invitations.'</em> And: <em>'Ethics-slop &mdash; vague normative language without testable claims.'</em> Marketing content scores Relevance 0.1, Quality 0.1 regardless of topic.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="prompt-item" style="--pi-color:var(--green)">
      <span class="prompt-icon">&sect;</span>
      <div class="prompt-label"><span class="prompt-title">Paper Detection</span><span class="prompt-sub">Academic papers flagged for enrichment</span></div>
      <div class="prompt-detail">Detects academic paper links for downstream enrichment &mdash; PDF download, abstract extraction, corpus ingestion. From the prompt: <em>'Check whether the content references or links to academic papers/preprints. Look for: arXiv URLs, DOI links, academic publisher URLs (nature.com, science.org, pnas.org, openreview.net, aclweb.org, etc.).'</em> Detected paper URLs are passed to the enrichment stage.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="prompt-item" style="--pi-color:#8892a6">
      <span class="prompt-icon">[+]</span>
      <div class="prompt-label"><span class="prompt-title">Err Toward Inclusion</span><span class="prompt-sub">25&ndash;30% target pass rate</span></div>
      <div class="prompt-detail">The prompt's default posture: when uncertain, let it through for human review rather than filtering it out. From the prompt: <em>'When in doubt about relevance, err toward higher scores &mdash; the lab team reviews after.'</em> Target pass rate is 25&ndash;30%. <em>'Do NOT shoehorn items into categories where they don't clearly belong.'</em></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="margin-top:28px;font-size:14px;color:var(--mint)">After Classification: Upsampling &amp; Delivery</h3>
  <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-2);margin-bottom:16px">Five stages transform classified items into structured records and route them to Slack. Hover or tap each stage for details.</p>

  <div class="pipeline-flow pipeline-flow--5" style="margin:16px 0 24px">
    <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--mint);cursor:pointer"
         data-ingest-tip="Generates a 5&ndash;10 word headline, assigns one of 16 categories, writes a classification reason, and flags paper links. Every item emerges with six scores, a category, a headline, and a reason."
         data-ingest-color="#2ec4b6">
      <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--mint)">Upsample</div>
      <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">Headlines + 16 categories</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--cyan);cursor:pointer"
         data-ingest-tip="Parallel Opus pass for long-form content (RSS, Substack, email, posts &gt;3K chars). Generates an intelligent reading &mdash; central insight first, supporting arguments with data, original word count. Honest about partial sources."
         data-ingest-color="#56b6c2">
      <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--cyan)">Summarise</div>
      <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">Opus, long-form only</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--amber);cursor:pointer"
         data-ingest-tip="Resolves shortlinks, scrapes abstracts from 30+ publisher domains, and downloads PDFs via publisher-specific URL transforms and the ANU institutional proxy."
         data-ingest-color="#f5a623">
      <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--amber)">Enrich</div>
      <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">Abstracts + PDFs</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--indigo);cursor:pointer"
         data-ingest-tip="Sorted by composite score and posted to daily #feed-{dayname} channels. Headline in bold, inline content or summary depending on length. Metadata footer with score, category, and reason. Abstracts and PDFs as thread replies."
         data-ingest-color="#818cf8">
      <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--indigo)">Post</div>
      <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">#feed-{'{'}day{'}'} channels</div>
    </div>
    <div class="pf-card" style="border-left:3px solid var(--pink);cursor:pointer"
         data-ingest-tip="Seth reviews #feed each morning and reacts with &#x1F44D;. The feed-promote daemon copies promoted messages to #firehose (including PDF attachments) and tracks IDs to prevent duplicates."
         data-ingest-color="#f472b6">
      <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--pink)">Promote</div>
      <div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-3)">&#x1F44D; &#x2192; #firehose</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="margin-top:24px;font-size:14px;color:var(--amber)">Intake Path 2: Manual Sharing</h3>

  <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin:12px 0 24px;padding:12px 16px;background:var(--bg-0);border-left:3px solid var(--amber)">
    <div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--amber)">share-to-minty</div>
    <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--text-2)">Real-time intake via Slack Socket Mode &mdash; URLs from any device bypass the daily batch.</div>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:2px">
      <code style="font-size:10px;padding:1px 6px;background:var(--bg-3);color:var(--text-3)">iPhone</code>
      <code style="font-size:10px;padding:1px 6px;background:var(--bg-3);color:var(--text-3)">Mac hotkey</code>
      <code style="font-size:10px;padding:1px 6px;background:var(--bg-3);color:var(--text-3)">Chrome ext</code>
      <code style="font-size:10px;padding:1px 6px;background:var(--bg-3);color:var(--text-3)">#minty-inbox</code>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="margin-top:28px;font-size:14px;color:var(--text-1)">Downstream: Three Readers on #firehose</h3>
  <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-2);margin-bottom:16px">Three daemons consume from <code style="font-size:12px">#firehose</code>, each for a different purpose. Hover or tap for details.</p>

  <div class="cards" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr))">
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--pink);cursor:pointer"
         data-ingest-tip="Generates a narrative daily digest from yesterday's #firehose posts &mdash; intelligent prose, not a list. Sent as HTML email to 29 lab members across 11 institutions, posted to #mint-community, and published to Ghost. A weekly &lsquo;Minty's Week in AI&rsquo; summary also ships before lab meetings."
         data-ingest-color="#f472b6">
      <div class="card-head"><div>
        <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--pink)">yesterday-in-ai</div>
        <div class="card-sub">Daily narrative digest &rarr; 29 lab members. Weekly summary for lab meetings.</div>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--purple);cursor:pointer"
         data-ingest-tip="Polls #firehose for messages with links lacking an attached PDF. Three-tier escalation: <strong>Tier 1</strong> &mdash; programmatic pattern matching against 30+ academic URL patterns (arXiv, OpenReview, bioRxiv). <strong>Tier 2</strong> &mdash; Twitter thread expansion via API to find paper URLs in self-reply chains. <strong>Tier 3</strong> &mdash; sandboxed Claude Opus agent (max 12 turns, 8 Bash calls) with Semantic Scholar, Unpaywall, and browser automation for paywalled content. PDFs uploaded as thread replies with canonical filenames."
         data-ingest-color="#a78bfa">
      <div class="card-head"><div>
        <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--purple)">news-pdf-bot</div>
        <div class="card-sub">3-tier PDF acquisition. Pattern matching &rarr; thread expansion &rarr; Claude agent.</div>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--teal);cursor:pointer"
         data-ingest-tip="Picks up papers from #firehose and runs the 11-stage ingestion pipeline: download, rename, markdown conversion, chunking, embedding, metadata extraction, cataloguing (Zotero), analysis (41 semantic questions), RAPTOR summaries, clustering, and Google Drive upload. Detailed in &sect;03 below."
         data-ingest-color="#2dd4bf">
      <div class="card-head"><div>
        <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--teal)">corpus-ingest</div>
        <div class="card-sub">11-stage pipeline &rarr; embedded, analyzed, searchable corpus. See &sect;03.</div>
      </div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="margin-top:24px;font-size:14px;color:var(--cyan)">The Result</h3>

  <p>Five minutes of morning review replaces hours of manual tracking. Everything worth following is captured, classified, summarized, stored, analyzed, and shared automatically.</p>
</Section>

<!-- ============ CORPUS INGESTION PIPELINE ============ -->
<Section id="corpus" num="03">
  <h2 class="cli-call" data-section-name="Corpus Ingestion"><span class="section-label">Corpus Ingestion</span><span class="cli-line"><span class="fn">Bash</span><span class="op">(</span><span class="str">"python3 corpus_ingest.py --stages=11"</span><span class="op">)</span><span class="cli-cursor"></span></span></h2>
  <p>The MINT Lab's intellectual engine: ~2,200 papers on AI safety, ethics, alignment, governance, and capabilities &mdash; all embedded, analyzed, and searchable.</p>

  <h3>Corpus-Ingest Pipeline Detail</h3>
  <p>Each paper flows through 11 stages in the unified corpus-ingest daemon. The pipeline supports resume from the last completed stage.</p>

  <div class="ingest-pipeline">
    <div class="ingest-stages">

      <div class="ingest-stage">
        <img class="ingest-dot" src="/mintresearch.org/assets/minty-teal.png" alt="" style="filter:drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(45,212,191,0.5))">
        <div class="ingest-line" style="background:#2dd4bf"></div>
        <div class="ingest-box" style="border-color:#2dd4bf" data-ingest-tip="Fetches PDFs from Slack (#firehose, #papers) or the local-PDFs catchup folder. SHA-256 hash deduplication prevents re-downloading papers already in the corpus. Supports arXiv, Semantic Scholar, direct PDF links, and 15+ publisher-specific download strategies." data-ingest-color="#2dd4bf">
          <span class="ingest-num" style="color:#2dd4bf">1</span>
          <div class="ingest-info">
            <div class="ingest-name" style="color:#2dd4bf">Download</div>
            <div class="ingest-desc">Slack + local PDFs</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ingest-stage">
        <img class="ingest-dot" src="/mintresearch.org/assets/minty-teal.png" alt="" style="filter:drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(45,212,191,0.5))">
        <div class="ingest-line" style="background:#2dd4bf"></div>
        <div class="ingest-box" style="border-color:#2dd4bf" data-ingest-tip="Extracts metadata (title, authors, year) from the PDF and renames the file to a standardised format: Author1_Author2_Year_ShortTitle.pdf. Uses CrossRef and Semantic Scholar APIs for metadata resolution." data-ingest-color="#2dd4bf">
          <span class="ingest-num" style="color:#2dd4bf">2</span>
          <div class="ingest-info">
            <div class="ingest-name" style="color:#2dd4bf">Rename</div>
            <div class="ingest-desc">Metadata extract</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ingest-stage ingest-stage--highlight">
        <img class="ingest-dot" src="/mintresearch.org/assets/minty-brown.png" alt="" style="filter:drop-shadow(0 0 5px rgba(251,146,60,0.6))">
        <div class="ingest-line" style="background:#fb923c"></div>
        <div class="ingest-box" style="border-color:#fb923c;border-width:1.5px;background:rgba(251,146,60,0.04)" data-ingest-tip="Converts PDF to searchable markdown via a 6-tier cascade: Companion (pre-extracted) &rarr; arXiv HTML &rarr; ar5iv &rarr; Marker &rarr; PyMuPDF &rarr; Tesseract OCR. Each tier is tried only if the previous fails. This is the most failure-prone stage — highlighted because conversion quality directly determines downstream embedding and analysis quality." data-ingest-color="#fb923c">
          <span class="ingest-num" style="color:#fb923c">3</span>
          <div class="ingest-info">
            <div class="ingest-name" style="color:#fb923c">Markdown</div>
            <div class="ingest-desc">6-tier cascade</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ingest-stage">
        <img class="ingest-dot" src="/mintresearch.org/assets/minty-indigo.png" alt="" style="filter:drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(129,140,248,0.5))">
        <div class="ingest-line" style="background:#818cf8"></div>
        <div class="ingest-box" style="border-color:#818cf8" data-ingest-tip="Generates 2048-dimensional vector embeddings via Voyage AI. Each document receives 48 separate embeddings — one per semantic dimension — enabling multi-lens retrieval. Chunks are also embedded separately for passage-level search." data-ingest-color="#818cf8">
          <span class="ingest-num" style="color:#818cf8">4</span>
          <div class="ingest-info">
            <div class="ingest-name" style="color:#818cf8">Embed</div>
            <div class="ingest-desc">Voyage 2048d</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ingest-stage">
        <img class="ingest-dot" src="/mintresearch.org/assets/minty-teal.png" alt="" style="filter:drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(45,212,191,0.5))">
        <div class="ingest-line" style="background:#2dd4bf"></div>
        <div class="ingest-box" style="border-color:#2dd4bf" data-ingest-tip="Fetches bibliographic metadata from CrossRef and Semantic Scholar: citation counts, DOI, publication venue, abstract, references, and author affiliations. Resolves arXiv IDs to published versions where available." data-ingest-color="#2dd4bf">
          <span class="ingest-num" style="color:#2dd4bf">5</span>
          <div class="ingest-info">
            <div class="ingest-name" style="color:#2dd4bf">Enrich</div>
            <div class="ingest-desc">CrossRef/S2</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ingest-stage">
        <img class="ingest-dot" src="/mintresearch.org/assets/minty-purple.png" alt="" style="filter:drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(167,139,250,0.5))">
        <div class="ingest-line" style="background:#a78bfa"></div>
        <div class="ingest-box" style="border-color:#a78bfa" data-ingest-tip="Deep semantic analysis via Claude Opus across 41 questions spanning research core (thesis, claims, evidence), methodology, AI-specific dimensions, meta-analysis, and advanced categories. Each answer becomes a searchable text field with its own 2048d embedding vector." data-ingest-color="#a78bfa">
          <span class="ingest-num" style="color:#a78bfa">6</span>
          <div class="ingest-info">
            <div class="ingest-name" style="color:#a78bfa">Analyze</div>
            <div class="ingest-desc">41Q via LLM</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ingest-stage">
        <img class="ingest-dot" src="/mintresearch.org/assets/minty-purple.png" alt="" style="filter:drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(167,139,250,0.5))">
        <div class="ingest-line" style="background:#a78bfa"></div>
        <div class="ingest-box" style="border-color:#a78bfa" data-ingest-tip="Generates hierarchical summaries at section and document level using Claude Opus. RAPTOR (Recursive Abstractive Processing for Tree-Organized Retrieval) summaries enable fast corpus-wide search via compact summary embeddings rather than full-text." data-ingest-color="#a78bfa">
          <span class="ingest-num" style="color:#a78bfa">7</span>
          <div class="ingest-info">
            <div class="ingest-name" style="color:#a78bfa">RAPTOR</div>
            <div class="ingest-desc">Summaries</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ingest-stage">
        <img class="ingest-dot" src="/mintresearch.org/assets/minty-teal.png" alt="" style="filter:drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(45,212,191,0.5))">
        <div class="ingest-line" style="background:#2dd4bf"></div>
        <div class="ingest-box" style="border-color:#2dd4bf" data-ingest-tip="Validates that all database fields are populated correctly: embeddings present, analysis complete, summaries generated, metadata resolved. Papers failing verification are flagged for manual review." data-ingest-color="#2dd4bf">
          <span class="ingest-num" style="color:#2dd4bf">8</span>
