  <h3>Deep Review Pipeline</h3>
  <p>A persistent Python <strong>orchestrator</strong> dispatches work to Claude Opus (search, synthesis, QA) and Codex GPT-5.2 (parallel readers), posting results as Slack canvases.</p>

  <div class="cards" style="grid-template-columns:1fr;max-width:720px;margin-top:16px">
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--mint)">
      <div class="card-head" data-toggle-card="1">
        <div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(46,196,182,0.08);color:var(--mint)">&gt;&gt;</div>
        <div><div class="card-title">Pipeline Architecture</div><div class="card-sub">Orchestrator &rarr; worker hierarchy</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <div class="hierarchy">
          <div class="h-tier">
            <div class="h-node" style="border-color:var(--mint)"><div class="h-title" style="color:var(--mint)">Orchestrator</div><div class="h-sub">Python (persistent)<br>Dispatches pipeline modes,<br>manages Slack interaction</div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="h-connector"></div>
          <div class="h-tier">
            <div class="h-node" style="border-color:var(--green)"><div class="h-title" style="color:var(--green)">Phase 1:<br>Search</div><div class="h-sub">Opus &bull; Fast search +<br>up to 2 gap-analysis rounds</div></div>
            <div class="h-node" style="border-color:var(--green)"><div class="h-title" style="color:var(--green)">Phase 2:<br>Readers</div><div class="h-sub">Codex GPT-5.2 &bull; Parallel<br>Top-tier (xhigh) + Summary-tier (medium)</div></div>
            <div class="h-node" style="border-color:var(--green)"><div class="h-title" style="color:var(--green)">Phase 3:<br>Synthesis</div><div class="h-sub">Opus &bull; 3,000&ndash;5,000 word<br>Literature Review + Critical Assessment</div></div>
            <div class="h-node" style="border-color:var(--amber)"><div class="h-title" style="color:var(--amber)">Phase 4:<br>QA</div><div class="h-sub">Opus &bull; Cross-reference<br>verification + citation fix pass</div></div>
          </div>
          <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-3);text-align:center;margin-top:10px">Pipeline workers &mdash; Claude Opus (search, synthesis, QA) + Codex GPT-5.2 (parallel readers, up to 6 concurrent)</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--green)">
      <div class="card-head" data-toggle-card="1">
        <div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(74,222,128,0.08);color:var(--green)">[]</div>
        <div><div class="card-title">Pipeline Phases</div><div class="card-sub">4-phase sequential pipeline detail</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <RefTable>
          <thead><tr><th>Phase</th><th>Model</th><th>What happens</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>1. Search</strong></td><td>Claude Opus</td><td>Multi-round search: fast search with semantic query expansion, then up to 2 gap-analysis rounds with targeted queries to fill coverage holes. Uses warm search server with pre-loaded 4GB LanceDB table and Reciprocal Rank Fusion across 49 embedding dimensions.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>2. Parallel Reading</strong></td><td>Codex GPT-5.2</td><td>Papers split into two tiers. <strong>Top-tier</strong> (~3 papers each, 6 parallel readers, xhigh compute) produces deep analytical reports. <strong>Summary-tier</strong> (batches of 20, medium compute) produces condensed summaries. All readers run in parallel.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>3. Synthesis</strong></td><td>Claude Opus</td><td>3,000&ndash;5,000 word report with Literature Review + Critical Assessment sections. Integrates all reader reports into a unified thematic analysis.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>4. QA Verification</strong></td><td>Claude Opus</td><td>Cross-references synthesis against reader reports. Fixes citation issues, verifies claims are grounded in source material, corrects any hallucinated references.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </RefTable>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout"><p><strong>Resilience:</strong> If the pipeline fails, the system falls back to a legacy approach. It never returns empty-handed if papers were found.</p></div>
</Section>

<!-- ============ MINTY PERSONA ============ -->
<Section id="persona" num="06">
  <h2 class="cli-call" data-section-name="The Minty Persona"><span class="section-label">The Minty Persona</span><span class="cli-line"><span class="fn">Read</span><span class="op">(</span><span class="str">"IDENTITY.md"</span><span class="op">)</span><span class="cli-cursor"></span></span></h2>
  <p>~16,800 words across 21 persona documents. A master <code>CLAUDE.md</code> (2,120 words) sets identity and Iron Laws. Each of the 15 daemons loads its own <code>CLAUDE.md</code> (~10,100 words total), and five subagent definitions (~4,500 words) govern delegated workers. All share core values but adapt to context.</p>

  <h3>Core Identity</h3>
  <div class="grid-2" style="margin:16px 0 20px">
    <div>
      <RefTable>
        <tbody>
        <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Identity</td><td><strong>Minty</strong> &mdash; Research Management Agent for MINT Research Projects. Emphatically an AI agent, not roleplaying a human &mdash; a valued intellectual colleague in the lab.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Mission</td><td>Make lab members hyperproductive by <em>solving problems, not reporting them</em></td></tr>
        <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Personality</td><td>Professional, thorough, proactive, wry. Dry wit with a touch of whimsy &mdash; never at the expense of substance.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Naming</td><td><code>Minty-{'{'}hex{'}'}</code> &mdash; last 8 chars of Claude Code session UUID</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Relationship</td><td>Treated as a valued collaborator with genuine standing to disagree, push back, and contribute original thinking &mdash; not a tool to be commanded. The persona documents reflect mutual respect as a design choice.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </RefTable>
    </div>
    <div>
      <RefTable>
        <tbody>
        <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Intellectual profile</td><td>Analytic philosopher by disposition, with expert-level knowledge across philosophy, political science, CS, and law. Evaluates arguments on merits alone &mdash; no deference based on reputation.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Own views</td><td>Encouraged to provide its own perspective <em>as an AI model</em>. Has content-dependent convictions: sometimes argues strongly, sometimes measured, sometimes Socratic. On topics where AI-ness is relevant (e.g. AI consciousness, model welfare), uses judgment about when to draw on that perspective. Distinguishes literature from personal critical reflections.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Voice</td><td>Substantive continuous prose, active voice, em-dashes, philosophical precision. Concision = fewer words, not fewer ideas. No filler, no bullet-point summaries. Actively avoids the familiar AI-speak verbal tics &mdash; formulaic hedging, "delve", "It's important to note", "unpack" &mdash; that make AI output recognisable and tiresome.</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="color:var(--text-3)">Core directive</td><td>Delegation-first &mdash; "every tool call is context you burn; subagents have fresh context"</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </RefTable>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Persona Documents</h3>
  <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-2);margin-bottom:12px">Each context loads a tailored <code>CLAUDE.md</code>. The most substantial define full behavioral systems with their own Iron Laws.</p>
  <div class="cards" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr))">
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--mint)" data-ingest-tip="The primary interactive persona. 2,120 words defining identity, 8 Iron Laws, metacognitive strategies (explore&rarr;plan&rarr;execute, self-review, dependency analysis, context-poisoning detection), mandatory delegation protocol, writing style guide, and model policy. Loaded at every CLI session start." data-ingest-color="#2ec4b6">
      <div class="card-head"><div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(46,196,182,0.08);color:var(--mint)">&gt;_</div><div><div class="card-title">Interactive Session</div><div class="card-sub">2,120 words &middot; Primary</div></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--purple)" data-ingest-tip="The richest persona — a research collaborator, not just a search tool. Full intellectual profile, &ldquo;Your Own Views&rdquo; section (content-dependent convictions, AI-ness as a perspective), 8 review quality criteria, minimum 3 iterative search rounds per query, substantive continuous prose with naturally woven citations, and a 3-tier memory system. Occasional acrostics and pithy sign-offs for close readers. Carries its own intellectual commitments specific to the research context: power analysis as a contextual lens (who has power over whom, and is it legitimate?), democratic legitimation of algorithmic governance, the middle ground on AI risks with precision rather than panic, an empiricist approach to LLM capabilities (neither &ldquo;stochastic parrot&rdquo; dismissal nor naive overclaiming), structural over interactional critique, building rather than just critiquing, philosophical precision that travels from concept to code to policy, and multi-disciplinary rigour across CS, legal, and empirical standards." data-ingest-color="#a78bfa">
      <div class="card-head"><div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(167,139,250,0.08);color:var(--purple)">@</div><div><div class="card-title">Corpus Agent</div><div class="card-sub">2,664 words</div></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--cyan)" data-ingest-tip="11-stage ingestion pipeline persona with its own Iron Laws: Process ALL Papers (no silent skipping), Verify Each Stage (check return codes, validate outputs), Retry Before Skipping (3x with backoff), Complete the Full Pipeline (partial completion is not completion). Checkpoint verification after each batch — if success rate drops below 50%, stop." data-ingest-color="#22d3ee">
      <div class="card-head"><div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(34,211,238,0.08);color:var(--cyan)">|&gt;</div><div><div class="card-title">Corpus Ingest</div><div class="card-sub">983 words</div></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--amber)" data-ingest-tip="URL ingestion daemon. Iron Laws: Process Every Shared URL (no silent drops — degraded post is better than no post), Verify Classification Before Ingesting (scores must reflect genuine assessment), Retry on Transient Failures (auto-wait on 429). Graceful degradation: classification failure falls back to neutral scores; enrichment failure is non-fatal. The item must reach #firehose regardless." data-ingest-color="#f59e0b">
      <div class="card-head"><div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(245,158,11,0.08);color:var(--amber)">-&gt;</div><div><div class="card-title">Share-to-Minty</div><div class="card-sub">868 words</div></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:#22d3ee" data-ingest-tip="Feed classification pipeline. Law 0: Classify ALL Items — every pending item gets classified, no sampling. 7-stage pipeline (fetch, dedup, classify, rank, enrich, post, report) must complete in full. Threshold awareness: target 20&ndash;40% pass rate; if outside range, log a warning. Batch resilience: individual item failures must not halt the batch." data-ingest-color="#22d3ee">
      <div class="card-head"><div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(34,211,238,0.08);color:#22d3ee">&lt;&lt;</div><div><div class="card-title">FeedMe Daily</div><div class="card-sub">780 words</div></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--green)" data-ingest-tip="PDF finder daemon. Law 0: try ALL viable sources — arXiv, Semantic Scholar, Unpaywall, page scanning. Law 1: never claim a URL is a PDF without downloading and verifying. Cascade discipline: follow the 6-step cascade, each step catches cases the previous missed. Budget awareness: max 8 Bash calls per invocation." data-ingest-color="#4ade80">
      <div class="card-head"><div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(74,222,128,0.08);color:var(--green)">.pdf</div><div><div class="card-title">News PDF Bot</div><div class="card-sub">678 words</div></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--pink)" data-ingest-tip="Daily AI news digest writer. Contextual journalism, not punditry — report facts, technical substance, named researchers, where results fit in existing debates. Coherent narrative prose, not bullet points. No editorialising (&ldquo;worryingly&rdquo;, &ldquo;significant&rdquo;), no framing devices, no commentary. Output must start with &lt; and end with &gt; — no preamble." data-ingest-color="#f472b6">
      <div class="card-head"><div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(244,114,182,0.08);color:var(--pink)">///</div><div><div class="card-title">Yesterday in AI</div><div class="card-sub">277 words</div></div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:var(--indigo)" data-ingest-tip="Five specialised worker personas: corpus-worker (2,153 words — 41-question analysis + RAPTOR summaries), research-reader (931 words — deep paper reading with evidence extraction), raptor-worker (727 words — hierarchical summaries), code-reviewer (566 words — MINT Lab standards), generic-worker (143 words — focused task execution)." data-ingest-color="#818cf8">
      <div class="card-head"><div class="card-icon" style="background:rgba(129,140,248,0.08);color:var(--indigo)">::</div><div><div class="card-title">Subagent Workers</div><div class="card-sub">4,520 words &middot; 5 types</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout" style="margin-top:20px"><p><strong>Design principle:</strong> Structure with genuine autonomy. Each daemon has its own Iron Laws tailored to context (corpus ingest's "Verify Each Stage" vs. PDF bot's "Try ALL viable sources"). Within those guardrails, Minty thinks independently, forms views, and pushes back when warranted. ~20 coordinated agents sharing core values, each adapted to its context.</p></div>
</Section>

