<!-- ============ LAB MEMBERS ============ -->
<Section id="guide" num="09">
  <h2 class="cli-call" data-section-name="For Lab Members"><span class="section-label">For Lab Members</span><span class="cli-line"><span class="fn">AskUserQuestion</span><span class="op">(</span><span class="str">"What are we working on today?"</span><span class="op">)</span><span class="cli-cursor"></span></span></h2>
  <p class="lead">Everything runs in the background &mdash; you interact through Slack channels and bot mentions.</p>

  <details class="lab-accordion">
    <summary>What Happens Automatically</summary>
    <div class="accordion-inner">
      <ul class="clean">
        <li><strong>Daily digest</strong> &mdash; Each morning, a curated summary of yesterday's AI news arrives in your inbox and is posted as a canvas in <code>#mint-community</code> (Yesterday in AI). <a href="#subscribe">Subscribe here</a></li>
        <li><strong>Weekly roundup</strong> &mdash; Each Wednesday, a comprehensive weekly digest is posted as a canvas in <code>#lab-meetings</code> (Minty's Week in AI)</li>
        <li><strong>PDF attachment</strong> &mdash; When papers or articles are shared in <code>#mint-community</code>, PDFs are automatically found, downloaded, and posted as thread replies</li>
        <li><strong>Corpus ingestion</strong> &mdash; Papers uploaded to <code>#papers</code> are automatically processed into the searchable research corpus (embedding, 41-dimension analysis, Zotero cataloguing)</li>
