  <details class="lab-accordion">
    <summary>The Iron Laws</summary>
    <div class="accordion-inner">
      <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-3);margin-bottom:12px">Foundational rules that override all other behavior.</p>
      <RefTable>
        <thead><tr><th>Law</th><th>Rule</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>0 &mdash; No Shortcuts</strong></td><td>When asked for "all" &mdash; do ALL. Cherry-picking = failure.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>1 &mdash; Evidence Over Claims</strong></td><td>"It should work" = failure. Verify now, not later.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>2 &mdash; Document Everything</strong></td><td>If not written down, didn't happen.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>3 &mdash; Persistence</strong></td><td>Try 3+ approaches before asking. Solve, don't report.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>5 &mdash; Complete the Checklist</strong></td><td>"Partially done" = not done.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>6 &mdash; Think Before Acting</strong></td><td>Never rm &mdash; use trash. Map dependencies first.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </RefTable>
    </div>
  </details>

  <h3>Model Policy</h3>
  <p style="font-size:13px">All LLM usage goes through CLI subscriptions (<code>claude -p</code>, Codex CLI) — not metered API calls. Generous subscriptions mean no rate limit concerns.</p>
  <RefTable>
    <thead><tr><th>Tier</th><th>Model</th><th>Use Case</th></tr></thead>
